
1994-10-07

# Chief Complaint
- Blurred Vision
- Memory Loss
- Thirst
- Fatigue
- Frequent Urination
- Confusion
- Hunger


# History of Present Illness
Elinor
 is a 82 year-old non-hispanic black female. Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), acute bronchitis (disorder), not in labor force (finding), limited social contact (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), sprain of ankle, viral sinusitis (disorder), laceration of forearm, social isolation (finding), stress (finding).

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is temporarily homeless. Patient has a documented history of opioid addiction. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a low socioeconomic background.
 Patient did not finish high school.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
acetaminophen 325 mg oral tablet; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet; insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]; carvedilol 25 mg oral tablet; acetaminophen 300 mg / hydrocodone bitartrate 5 mg oral tablet; naproxen sodium 220 mg oral tablet; meperidine hydrochloride 50 mg oral tablet; abuse-deterrent 12 hr oxycodone hydrochloride 15 mg extended release oral tablet; losartan potassium 50 mg oral tablet; furosemide 40 mg oral tablet

# Assessment and Plan


## Plan

# Assessment and Plan


## Plan

The following procedures were conducted:
- assessment of health and social care needs (procedure)
- medication reconciliation (procedure)
The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]
- carvedilol 25 mg oral tablet
- hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet
- furosemide 40 mg oral tablet
- losartan potassium 50 mg oral tablet
- 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet

 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a low socioeconomic background.
 Patient did not finish high school.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
acetaminophen 325 mg oral tablet; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet; insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]; carvedilol 25 mg oral tablet; acetaminophen 300 mg / hydrocodone bitartrate 5 mg oral tablet; naproxen sodium 220 mg oral tablet; meperidine hydrochloride 50 mg oral tablet; abuse-deterrent 12 hr oxycodone hydrochloride 15 mg extended release oral tablet; losartan potassium 50 mg oral tablet; furosemide 40 mg oral tablet

# Social History

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is temporarily homeless. Patient has a documented history of opioid addiction. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a low socioeconomic background.
 Patient did not finish high school.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), acute bronchitis (disorder), not in labor force (finding), limited social contact (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), sprain of ankle, viral sinusitis (disorder), social isolation (finding), stress (finding).

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is temporarily homeless. Patient has a documented history of opioid addiction. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a low socioeconomic background.
 Patient did not finish high school.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
acetaminophen 325 mg oral tablet; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet; insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]; acetaminophen 300 mg / hydrocodone bitartrate 5 mg oral tablet; naproxen sodium 220 mg oral tablet; meperidine hydrochloride 50 mg oral tablet; abuse-deterrent 12 hr oxycodone hydrochloride 15 mg extended release oral tablet

 is a 75 year-old non-hispanic black female. Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), not in labor force (finding), limited social contact (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), social isolation (finding), stress (finding).

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is temporarily homeless. Patient has a documented history of opioid addiction. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a low socioeconomic background.
 Patient did not finish high school.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet; insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]; naproxen sodium 220 mg oral tablet; meperidine hydrochloride 50 mg oral tablet

Patient is presenting with part-time employment (finding). 

## Plan

- assessment of health and social care needs (procedure)
- assessment of anxiety (procedure)
- assessment using morse fall scale (procedure)
- screening for domestic abuse (procedure)
- depression screening (procedure)
- depression screening using patient health questionnaire two-item score (procedure)
The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]
- hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet
- 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet

Patient comes from a low socioeconomic background.
 Patient did not finish high school.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet; insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]; naproxen sodium 220 mg oral tablet; meperidine hydrochloride 50 mg oral tablet

# Assessment and Plan


## Plan

The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]
- hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet
- 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet

- insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]

The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]
- hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet
- 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet



1968-05-03

# Chief Complaint
- Blurred Vision
- Memory Loss
- Thirst
- Fatigue
- Frequent Urination
- Confusion
- Hunger


# History of Present Illness
Elinor
 is a 56 year-old non-hispanic black female. Patient has a history of hypertension, miscarriage in first trimester, body mass index 40+ - severely obese (finding), hyperlipidemia, osteoarthritis of knee, lack of access to transportation (finding), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), only received primary school education (finding), not in labor force (finding), diabetic renal disease (disorder), chronic kidney disease stage 1 (disorder), metabolic syndrome x (disorder), hypertriglyceridemia (disorder), anemia (disorder), diabetes, transport problems (finding), body mass index 30+ - obesity (finding), hyperglycemia (disorder).

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is temporarily homeless. Patient has a documented history of opioid addiction. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a low socioeconomic background.
 Patient did not finish high school.
Patient currently has Blue Cross Blue Shield.

# Allergies
animal dander (substance), eggs (edible) (substance), tree pollen (substance)

# Medications
simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg oral tablet; insulin human, isophane 70 unt/ml / regular insulin, human 30 unt/ml injectable suspension [humulin]; vitamin b 12 5 mg/ml injectable solution; naproxen sodium 220 mg oral tablet; meperidine hydrochloride 50 mg oral tablet

- Fatigue
- Frequent Urination
- Confusion
- Hunger


# History of Present Illness
Elinor
 is a 24 year-old non-hispanic black female. Patient has a history of miscarriage in first trimester, body mass index 40+ - severely obese (finding), lack of access to transportation (finding), transport problems (finding), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), only received primary school education (finding), body mass index 30+ - obesity (finding).

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is temporarily homeless. Patient has a documented history of opioid addiction. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a low socioeconomic background.
 Patient did not finish high school.
Patient currently has UnitedHealthcare.

# Allergies
animal dander (substance), eggs (edible) (substance), tree pollen (substance)

# Medications
No Active Medications.

# Assessment and Plan


## Plan

The patient was placed on a careplan:
- routine antenatal care
